Cell.Data: Looks like a stray… You all alone?
You are? You could tag along with me if you want. I have to warn you, though, we’ll be getting into some trouble…
Well then, if you’re sure, who am I to stop you? Let’s get going, shall we?
Don’t worry, safe to approach. Just don’t make any sudden moves.
Name’s Ilthain, I’m out here hunting a Svriir. It scorched a gang of slavers to a crisp near Archion – been sent to kill it.
Archion? The flying city? You’re a long way from home – the nearest anchor isn’t exactly close…
Believe me, I didn’t want to make the trip – was glad the bastard slavers died. Order knows it as well. Sending me out here’s a funny joke they’re telling each other.
You’re a part of this “Order,” I assume?
That’s right – The Order of Oshara. We ride drakes and chase Svriir, apparently…
Speaking of which, need to get back after the beast. Want to tag along? Aeldor here’s spooked, not sure what’s got him like this…
Any case, wouldn’t say no to another pair of fighting hands.
It’s why I’m here. It’s been slaughtering Stormfall’s citizens, so there’s no shortage of people that need the beast dead.
Guess that’s settled then. Think I saw the beast heading towards a cave system up ahead – should get on its trail.
Got more than Svriir to worry about, by the looks of it.
Must’ve been what Aeldor was so spooked about. Not much scares him, either – can’t be good.
Best get back to work then, more lives at stake than I thought.
Yes, whatever this “phenomenon” thing is, it’s making the Svriir act up.
You mentioned the Order of Oshara earlier. I’ve never heard of them.
Not surprised. Order tends to keep to themselves. Wouldn’t want me educating you, either. They have their reasons. Not good ones though.
So what can you tell me?
Well, that “Oshara” is a Dragon, a Matriarch, to be exact; we’re her protectors, in return for her guidance.
That’s how it’s supposed to be, but we don’t let that hold us back, oh no; we got a much broader range of activities we like to “partake” in:
Let’s see, we’ve got “resolving petty disputes,” uh… “pushing for certain policy decisions,” and… oh, best of all, “making sure slavers know how valued and respected they are.”
Oof, I’m sensing a little bitterness here…
At least a little – but whatever, I’ve said enough, let’s remember why we’re here.
Should hurry, looks like you got greater problems than the Svriir.
Glad that’s over… should be the end of our Svriir problem, though.
That’s not all that’s bothering you, is it? That “phenomenon” got you worried?
That, for one, but… I also worry for my family – fate has pulled us apart, and I don’t know if it can be fixed…
Sorry to hear that – families aren’t easy…
Sorry, I shouldn’t dwell on it, it’s not your problem…
Don’t sweat it. Family’s important, worth worrying about – and fighting for.
Yes… What about you? What will you do now?
Now? Mmmh, well, guess I’ll go back to the Order. Enjoy the look on the Elders’ faces when they see I’m still alive and kicking.
They’d prefer that you weren’t? Why?
Ah, the story’s a long one. Short of it is, they don’t want me to be Elder. I’d just ruin their schemes, preach Oshara’s teachings – they wouldn’t like that.
It sounds like you’ve got your work cut out for you.
Yeah, you could say that. Nothing I’m not used to, though.
Well, then, I guess this is where we part ways. Perhaps our paths will cross again.
If you find yourself in Archion, come look for me – know a good place to drown our sorrows. Plus, the view’s always nice to look at.
Greetings, {mylord|mylady}. I’m not sure if you’ve noticed, but we seem to have attracted a small population of drakes to the city.
They belong to the Order of Oshara. Their Matriarch, the very same Oshara, has gone missing, and they’ve come here looking for her –
Saying that they’re desperate would be an understatement.
Ah, the Order of Oshara – I’ve met one of their knights before…
Yes, a knight named Ilthain, I think? He asked for you specifically.
Ilthain?! Yes, I know him, he’s a good man… but why is he looking for Oshara here?
I hope you don’t mind, but we sent for them while you were away.
We’ve been hearing reports of “flying serpents” over the Stormfall Wilds, and the Order are the only ones we know of that have dealings with dragons…

{Mylord|Mylady}, if I may be so bold… It may be in Stormfall’s best interests to assist the Order. Archion is a close ally of ours, and the Order is well respected in the upper echelons of their society…
If we were to help them save their Matriarch, it would go a long way to strengthening our bond with Archion.
Oh good, well as long as it’s in Stormfall’s best interests, then I see no reason to delay.
Very good, {mylord|mylady}. Ilthain and the other knights are in the palace waiting for you.
Never imagined you as regent… can’t believe it. How’s the high life treating you?
Can’t say I’m enjoying the constant manoeuvring… But I’m doing my best to do some good.
Excuse me, sorry to interrupt, but we do have a crisis on our hands…
Right, yes, sorry… Regent, this is Ondar, Elder of the Order – one of the good ones… About why we’re here –
Yes, I was told of Oshara’s disappearance. And seeing as you helped Stormfall in its time of need, we’ll be happy to return the favour.
Hoping you’d say that… You should know, though – this is a big deal, Oshara is more important than the stuff I told you…
If Stormfall’s going to help, they deserve to know what’s at stake…
What’s he talking about? If there’s something I need to know, then tell me. Now.
Hmm… fine… Go ahead, Ilthain. I admit it may be unwise to keep secrets at this point.
Right, okay… So Oshara, she’s the child of this ancient creature, Naedre, and Naedre keeps this plane of existence connected to the others…
These other “planes,’ they got power – power people want. Oshara helps Naedre keep the paths to them shut.
Without Oshara, Naedre loses her voice…
Yeah, her voice… and without that… Argh, look. It will be really bad for everyone if something happens to Oshara. That’s it, we… we just can’t let it happen.
Okay, Ilthain, then we won’t… I’m still not sure I fully understand, but…
Even if what you’re saying is nonsense… I owe you one. If you say she needs saving, then I’m with you…
I’ll have Thunderblade Zalahir work with you both on strategy.
I have already spoken to him. He said that you would be eager to help.
We got a command tent outside the city. Meet us there when you’re ready.
We’ve flown as close to the Republic camp as we can; it’s well defended.
Cannons, lots of them, aimed at the sky.
The drakes are here. Locked up. Haven’t seen Oshara with them… We need to get inside…
With those cannons operational, our capacity to attack from the skies is limited.
We spotted three generators in the camp. They keep the cannons supplied with power.
Then they need to be destroyed… I’ll handle the generators; once they’re down, unleash everything we have.
We won’t hold back, don’t you worry…
Oh, and just be warned, going to get very hot in there…
I’m sure I can handle it…
I don’t like this. There should be more of us out here.
You! You shouldn’t have come here.
Good shot by the way. A clean kill.
Should keep our squad fed for at least a week. Maybe two.
Unless Lucan decides to feed it to the drakes…
He better hadn’t, we worked hard for this –
That may be so, but our beloved commander likes to keep his drake well fed, and, well, he’s the commander, so our kill is his kill.
Yes, yes, you’re right, of course…
Should be nearing the camp soon – I need to find those generators.
Can’t see a thing… At least the Punishers have those pyres to see if anything’s coming at them.
One of these gates must lead to where the drakes are being held. Need to bring down those energy fields first…
They must be hooked up to the generators…
What do we have here? Come, it must be eradicated.
You’re not one of us! Punishers! Crush the interloper!
You go no further than this, worm.
How did y – Punishers! We have a pest in our midst. You know what to do.
I hear your pitter-patter, little mouse. It is time for you to squeal.
Wait, listen. On the other side of the gate. I heard something.
Ready your weapons. Something’s not right. There’s fighting beyond the gate.
How’s Dale doing, do you know? He doesn’t say much.
I’m not sure he’s ever going to recover…
Imagine losing an entire leg, I can’t believe the beast just bit the thing clean off…
To be honest, I’d rather be dead than have only one leg.
I’m awake, you wretches! If you really have to talk about me, at least have the decency to do it outside!
No, you didn’t – now just shut up and leave me in peace.
He doesn’t recognize me sometimes, my father. I knew it was only a matter of time, but still…
It comes for us all eventually… Do you think there’s any hope? Not everyone in the Republic starts losing their memories in middle age, do they?
No, not all, but most do. Although… I hear there’s ways of fortifying your mind, make sure it keeps your memories safe. The ways of witchcraft, that is…
Woah woah woah, stop talking. Do you want to get us killed?
But it’s true, I’ve heard the rumours –
No, we are not going there. Leave it alone.
Fine, you leave it to fate, then, but perhaps when your memories start to fade, you’ll begin to feel differently.
Lucan claims to have seen a dragon once, when he was a child. As in, a fully grown dragon, not like these little ones we have.
Seriously? Come on then, let’s hear it.
He says that when he was a child, the beast attacked his home, engulfed his entire village in flames.
He only survived because he jumped into a well. He waited there for hours…
At one point, the dragon looked down into the well, right into his eyes. He believes the beast blessed him with that look.
If you ask me, it was probably just another Svriir. Lots of them can breathe fire and have those serpent eyes.
Hey, you think whatever you want, I’m just telling you the story…
Rally to me! The generator must be protected!
We have to stop them here! They cannot be allowed to reach the other generators!
This ends here… Infantry! Cut the intruder down!
Blast it! That’s our last generator!
H-How did they get past our defences! We’re completely exposed out here!
Now, while they have nowhere to run! The intruder goes no further than this!
Affirmative! They will not get past us!
Can’t let them stop me, I need to break through…
Their commander. Heard them calling him Lucan. Need to have a little chat with him – might have answers about Oshara…
Keep going, we’ll try to injure his drake, force him to land up ahead.
Right, that’s the last of them… I should push on.
Here I was, thinking I’d have to sneak into your fancy new Palace. I admit, I was quite looking forward to the challenge.
But alas, this will have to do.
Keep shocking him! We nearly have him!
Time for you to get back in your cage, DR-2.
I should try to free Oshara’s drakes if I can – the Republic has enough weapons of war without adding fire-breathing reptiles to the list.
Got you, Republic scum… Regent! Lucan’s coming to you!
We’ll cover you from up here, block his escape. Now finish the bastard.
Stop the intruder! Lucan will not abide losing a single drake!
These drakes are the property of Lucan’s Talons now. You were a fool to come here.
Lucan has made us the envy of the Republic. You will not take that from us!
Their flames will consume you all. It is inevitable. We will not be stopped.
You – I know you. You’re one of those “Children of Heimlock,’ aren’t you? One of his traitors.
But don’t worry, whether you’re a traitor or not is of little consequence to me.
I’ll be killing you for my claim to these beasts, not for the good of my beloved Republic…
You’re looking for her, aren’t you? The big one. She’s not here, I’m afraid…
Bastards… That was hardly – a fair fight
Alright, so you have my attention. Now, what could you possibly want from me?
The drakes. Where’d you get them?
Yes, yes, they’re her children, I took them from their mother, how upsetting. But no, we don’t have her…
Now, the people that do have her, they talked about you and your ragged band of knights quite a bit; they knew you’d come flying… and here you are.
Who’re you talking about? Who has her?
Oh, well I really couldn’t say…
Do you ever have that? Sometimes your memories just seem to get lost in all the noise of existence. A shame, I would have loved to have helped…
Stop toying with us, Lucan. Answer his questions.
Oh, I’m sorry, was there something you wanted to know?
You know what we want. Now talk.
Oof, I was almost scared there for a second…
Not going to talk? Fine. Then we’ll make you talk. And when we’re done, we won’t kill you, not right away, no…
Want you to be awake when we feed you to the drakes… They’ll eat you, piece by piece – how’s that sound?
Sounds perfectly reasonable to me. This is assuming, of course, that you’ll ever make me talk…
I’ve heard enough of this. Ilthain. Tie him up and gag him, we will figure out how to get answers once we’re back in Stormfall.
Give me two minutes with him. I’ll make him talk.
No, we are taking him back. Those are my orders. There are other ways to make a man talk.
Argh, alright… Hope you’re right about this. Regent, we’ll see you back in Stormfall.
Don’t worry, we’ll get the answers we need.
No, Ilthain has tried beating him… a lot, but that has yet to show any signs of working.
Perhaps, but we have to consider other solutions.
Other solutions? What other solutions could there possibly be?
Maybe he has loved ones, something we could use as leverage…
And what makes you think he’d tell us he has “loved ones”?
Wait a second, you’re way off here. From my experience, resistance like this only comes from chemical enhancement. Trust me, I’d know –
It wouldn’t be the first time the Republic has pumped its soldiers full of chemicals to stop them talking.
That would make sense… Does Stormfall have alchemists? Perhaps they could find a way to negate the chemical’s effects?
We do – I’ll call Oshara’s Council, have Zalahir set the alchemists to work on a concoction. It shouldn’t take them long, once they’ve figured out the chemical affecting him.
If it’ll get us our answers…. I’m all for it.
You would have thought they’d offer to give me a ride…
There they are, looks like they’ve been busy…
You’re here! Look, we found a Republic scout, must be one of Lucan’s…
Wh – what? Who… who… are you...?
Listen to me… where is she, where is Oshara? What did you find in there?
Ritual? Corrupting? That doesn’t sound good.
No… It’s not… They’re going to corrupt her… make her an abomination… We need to get in there, before it’s too late… Naedre have mercy on us all…
We will have to dismount and enter the caves on foot. There’s not enough room for the drakes.
No, that’ll take too long, and we’re weaker without the drakes… We’ll fly over the caves, find a larger entrance somewhere.
Ilthain, do not be foolish. We have no guarantee that there will be another entrance.
I don’t care, there has to be. If I have the other knights, we can split up, increase our chances. If we go on foot, we’ll never make it in time.
He’s right, we don’t know how long it’ll take to reach her.
Mmmm… Fine. lthain, take the others and find another entrance. Regent, you can’t fly, so you and I will enter the caves on foot. Let’s move.
Listen up. Oshara’s in grave danger. Cult of the Aberrant have her, got her in some blasted ritual.
Entrance here’s too small for drakes, so we’re going to fly over, find another way in…
We’ll split up – it’ll increase our chances. If you find her, don’t wait, you get inside and you kill the damned wretches hurting her…
Give everything, and with Naedre’s mercy guiding us, we will bring Oshara home.
Now, get going, all of you!
Ashtaroth’s magic is strong here… We will need Naedre’s blessing to nullify it…
I will cast the spell, but you must stay close…
Only the abominations affected by the spell will be weakened.
Now! Get them! Tear the flesh from their bones!
There’s a lot of them… They really don’t want us getting through, do they?
Stay close to me! We need to get through them, quickly!
Regent I – I am afraid of what will happen to Ilthain and I if we fail…
For years, the Order has been trying to push us out…
You see, Ilthain he – he was once a slave… And the Order – they cannot abide an ex-slave inheriting my position as Elder…
For them, maintaining blood ties to the founders is paramount…
But I digress, we must focus on what is before us. Oshara’s safety comes first.
Stop them! Lord Belizul wants them dead!
Let’s give them their pound of flesh…
Ondar, about Ilthain… he never told me he was a slave.
Why would he? The Order does not let him forget it…
Why does he stay? He must hate them.
He does… but he knows Oshara’s importance, and fights for her to be heard. It has been a long time since the Order valued her guidance…
And if she dies today, they will be beyond redemption… Let’s keep moving.
Grind their bones into the dirt! They must be stopped!
Belizul, mylord… some of Oshara’s knights are looking for another entrance. It won’t be long before they discover the tunnels…
It matters little. The ritual will be complete long before they manage to find a way through the labyrinth.
I was thinking… shouldn’t we just – kill her? Isn’t that what he wanted us to do?
It is, but our master, Ashtaroth, has other plans… You would do well to remember that.
Yes, of – of course, my lord…
Did you hear that? Is that her?
It must be… It’s a good sign, it means she’s still resisting… Come on! Let’s hurry!
Belizul – mylord – they are nearing the inner sanctum…
Then it seems as though I will be forced to intervene… Tell our remaining forces to make their way to the inner sanctum. It is time for me to take on a more perfect form…
We need to be quick. If she’s in there for too long we will lose her completely.
Where’s Ilthain? Surely he found a way through?
Don’t worry about him, he will be here! Just keep fighting!
I must admit, I am surprised you made it this far. Not many manage to find their way through the murky waters of the Garadalug Bowels.
But you will not stop this. Oshara belongs to him now, the Lord of Flesh… Ashtaroth.
I’ve dealt with far worse, and far bigger, than you – your fate will be no different to the Lambach’s…
It’s only a matter of time. Her mind is slipping away.
Argh! Quiet, demon! This is not over… not yet.
If you stop now, you can leave here in peace… Why torture yourself with the visage of your Matriarch, made aberrant by Ashtaroth’s touch?
No… there’s still time – time to save her.
Look at you, even you do not believe the words you speak. Do not ignore what is right in front of you.
Ok… Leg’s broken, so not going to be much use against Oshara…
You shouldn’t blame yourself, you know.
Feels like I should, I was the one that pushed Ondar to split us up.
Right, and in another world, that plan might have paid off… but it didn’t, and now we have to deal with it.
This is just the way it is. We make tough decisions, and more often than not, we get them wrong.
But we have to have the will to keep making those decisions – right the wrongs of the ones that came before. If we don’t… we may as well accept defeat.
Ok… Let’s deal with what’s in front us… Need to find Oshara, and… put her down…
Checked with Zalahir, he’s heard scattered reports: villages burning, wildfires – has to be her. Trouble is finding her, can’t chase her round the continent.
Meet me at Oshara’s Council, I’ll have Zalahir organize a scouting mission.
Good idea. She’ll probably carve out a territory for herself. Find that, find Oshara.
This must be it, the Sunken Lands… Scorched flesh on the air… She’s been here…
Oshara… sounds like she’s in pain…
In the embers, can you hear them? So warm, so sweet… they whisper to me, soothe me…
All these bodies… Is this how Oshara will be remembered?
We should go… It could come back at any moment.
Please… kill me. I feel… everything… it’s all wrong, so very wrong… please… put an end to this…
We’ll be together soon… I… I can feel it – my soul – clawing at my chest… All I need – a blade… to cut it loose…
Have you seen Jared? I thought he was behind us…
Oshara, if there’s a part of you in there, listen to me… Think of Ilthain, and the drakes, your children. Think of Naedre… they need you.
Ilthain was right… I have no choice…
She’s heading further east, deeper into the Sunken Lands. I need to stay on her trail.
Incubation pods? The Cult of the Aberrant… they’re here to finish it, stake Ashtaroth’s claim to Oshara for good.
The people inside were probably dragged from the caravans. I should put them out of their misery…
Burned to a crisp… The Cult must be in pursuit…
Keep your magic focused, we nearly have her!
They’re trying to subdue her… I need to end this
The Republic? They must be trying to capture her, the same way they captured her children…
She’s beyond their control now, but I have to make sure…
I’ll do what needs to be done…
She’s badly hurt… She won’t be able to fly much further…
Look at them all, fighting over the right to wield her… fools, all of them!
Keep firing, she can’t take much more!
They almost had her then… I’m coming Oshara, it’s nearly over…
You’re not going to make this easy for me, are you…?
Fight this Oshara! It’s not too late!
There really is only one way this is going to end…
I should take the egg back to Ilthain. He’ll know what to do with it…
You’re back… I - I felt it, her heart giving out…
Before she died, Oshara gave me something. An egg… It has a Matriarch growing inside it –
A Matriarch egg? I didn’t think that was possible…
She’s to become the next voice of Naedre – to replace Oshara. That’s what I was told.
If that’s true… She needs protection… could take her to the Order… I’d be punished for my failure here, but – but maybe it’s what’s best, if it keeps her safe…
You want to trust the Order with this? You, of all people, want to trust them?
I… Ugh, no, I can’t – I don’t know what they’d do with a Matriarch whelp. Whatever it is, wouldn’t help her or Naedre, know that for sure…
Ok… So I don’t take the egg to the Order…
You – you should take it. The Matriarch’ll be safest with you –
You have power, and a city behind you – if anyone is prepared for what comes next, it’s you… It… This is the best decision I can make…
Okay Ilthain, but you don’t have to leave, you can stay here – you should stay here. You knew Oshara best – you should be around to raise her whelp…
… You’re right – and not like there’s a home in the Order for me now, not with Ondar gone…
Oh, and another thing… Oshara said that only the new Matriarch “can soothe.’ But soothe what? Do you know what she meant?
Mmmh, well… Oshara was Naedre’s voice, as you know. Naedre’ll get restless without it.
Don’t know what that means for us – this world – but it’s not going to be good…
Best guess – the new Matriarch will have a part to play in whatever happens next…
Then what should we do now?
For now… be vigilant, keep the Matriarch safe, and be ready to act. Nothing to do but wait… Naedre – she’ll give us a sign…
Okay, then we wait. When the time comes, I’ll be ready.
{Mylord|Mylady}. We’ve just been discussing the reports coming in from the Stormfall Wilds.
We need to verify them, pinpoint where the “flying serpents” are coming from – see if they’re connected to Oshara.
We suspect they may be her youngest progeny – the last time we saw her she had a new brood of eggs.
If the drakes are Oshara’s, we’ll be one step closer to finding her…
With that in mind, I’ve begun briefing our scouts for an investigation of the Stormfall Wilds.
{Mylord,|Mylady,} when you are ready, gather Oshara’s Council. We shall dispatch the scouts on your order.
{Mylord,|Mylady,} our scouts are on standby to investigate the reports of drakes in the Wilds. Give the word and they will be dispatched.
By your will, I’ll give the orders to our scouts.
Tell us when you have something, we’ll be ready.
{Mylord|Mylady}, our scouts have returned from the Wilds… Assemble Oshara’s Council and I will relay the contents of their report..
{Mylord|Mylady}, our scouts have returned… It seems the Republic has set up camp in the Wilds. They… have drakes under their control.
Got to be Oshara’s! How the hell’d the Republic get their hands on them?
How, indeed… We should not waste any more time… Ilthain, we will go ahead and devise a plan of attack. Regent, meet us there when you are ready.
Our assault on the Republic drake-taming operation… Lucan was tough to crack…
{Mylord|Mylady}, Lucan still refuses to talk. I’ve had alchemists run some tests on him, and he is under the effects of a pain-blocking chemical, as you suspected…
At your command, they will work on a concoction to negate its effects.
We’ll have a concoction ready as soon as possible. We should have our answers soon.
{Mylord|Mylady}. The concoction worked. Ilthain was able to make Lucan talk. Gather Oshara’s Council and we will relay the news… I’m afraid it’s not good…
There you are, beginning to think you hadn’t got the news… Lucan talked…
Yes, he talked, but the news is not good…
Zalahir says you have experience with The Cult of the Aberrant. The servants of Ashtaroth, Fallen Lord of Flesh.
If what Lucan says is true, this cult have Oshara in a place called the Garadalug Bowels –
Oshara’s warned us before, how Ashtaroth can twist the minds of the dragons… If they do that to her… Who knows how it will unbalance Naedre…
We will mobilize the other knights and leave as soon as possible… Meet us there, Regent, and do not delay too long.
We were so close to saving her…
{Mylord|Mylady}, I presume you have heard the reports? Oshara has been busy…
She’s showing no signs of stopping… We need to get to her, soon…
I’ve gathered volunteers for a scouting operation, to see if they can pinpoint her whereabouts. Just give the order.
I’ve gathered volunteers for the scouting operation, the bravest we have. They will do what they have to do.
We’ll send news when we’ve found her. The rest will be up to you…
Our scouts have pinpointed Oshara’s whereabouts. Assemble what’s left of Oshara’s Council, and we shall discuss it further.
We have been tracking Oshara’s activity, and she appears to be most active over the Sunken Lands, to the East. If she has a lair, that is where it will be.
The remaining knights would like to accompany you…
As would the Thunderblades, {mylord|mylady}, we will fight by your side…
No. Ilthain, you and your men have suffered enough, I would not see them kill their own Matriarch.
As for you Zalahir, I need you and your men to keep the city safe. Man the Radiant Turrets and aim at the sky, should I fail, you’ll need them.
There you are, been waiting for you.
There is plenty on the agenda, {mylord|mylady}.
I have assembled the council. We have plenty of matters to discuss.
Ah good, you’re here, let’s get to business.
What is on the agenda today, {mylord|mylady}?
You’re back. Got anything specific you want to talk about?
We will send Thunderblades at once. The Order’s supplies will be recovered, I will make sure of it.
The lost supplies have been found; we will hand them over to the Order immediately.
The lost supplies have been located; Thunderblades will be dispatched to recover them, {mylord|mylady}.
Our Thunderblades managed to retrieve the supplies. They’re back in the Order’s possession, {mylord|mylady}.
Thunderblades will be dispatched, {mylord|mylady}. They will not rest until the supplies are returned.
The Order’s supplies have been returned to them. They should have more at their disposal from this point forward.
We will work on getting those supplies for the Order.
We will have the Order restocked as soon as we can.
